## üîß Development Strategy & Implementation
The development strategy involves implementing the Bootstrap Card as a functional component using React TypeScript. The component will accept data through props, allowing for flexibility and reusability. A time estimate of 24 hours is allocated for implementation, including testing and documentation. The following considerations should be prioritized:

*   **Code Architecture**: Implement as a modular, reusable component.
*   **Accessibility**: Use appropriate ARIA attributes and keyboard interactions.
*   **Responsiveness**: Use CSS media queries to ensure responsiveness.
*   **Testing**: Write unit tests to ensure functionality and prevent regressions.
*   **Props**: Type all props using TypeScript interfaces for type safety.
*   **Error Handling**: Gracefully handle missing or invalid data.

```typescript
import React from 'react';

interface CardProps {
  title: string;
  description: string;
  imageUrl?: string;
  linkUrl?: string;
  ariaLabel?: string;
}

const Card: React.FC<CardProps> = ({ title, description, imageUrl, linkUrl, ariaLabel }) => {
  return (
    <div className="card" aria-label={ariaLabel || title}>
      {imageUrl && <img src={imageUrl} alt={title} className="card-image" />}
      <div className="card-body">
        <h2 className="card-title">{title}</h2>
        <p className="card-description">{description}</p>
        {linkUrl && (
          <a href={linkUrl} className="card-link">
            Learn More
          </a>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Card;
```

